  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>Okay, this is totally great.

Sorry that "git merge" and you got into a fight, and time lost. Hopefully we can
prevent that through <a href="https://openhatch.org/bugs/issue253">https://openhatch.org/bugs/issue253</a> .

I'm going to deploy this right now, because it's too awesome to hold back on. I
have some feedback that maybe is worth responding to.

* For me, as I look at <a href="http://127.0.0.1:8000/missions/tar,">http://127.0.0.1:8000/missions/tar,</a> it's somewhat strange
to have the top blue line of the &lt;div class="head"&gt; be overlapping with the rock
face. I know that's the way the rest of them work, but I wonder what you think.

* The CSS you added to to templates/missions/main.html would be better if it
were in a .css file. Something we often do is give the &lt;body&gt; tag on certain
pages like that a specific class so you can put that in your selector. See e.g.
mysite/project/templates/edit_project.html

* It'd be great to have the source files. For those, a somewhat unusual process:
Go to <a href="http://gitorious.org/openhatch/oh-bigfiles">http://gitorious.org/openhatch/oh-bigfiles</a> and click "Clone repository",
then clone your personal oh-bigfiles repo, and add the source files, and do a
"git push". Then ping me here, and I'll merge that into the main oh-bigfiles repo.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
